<TITLE> Inter hit by injuries for title tilt </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MILAN, May 10 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Brief news from Serie A ahead of Sunday's penultimate round of matches (kick offs 1300 GMT) Inter Milan, who will seal the title with a home win over Siena, will almost certainly be without Zlatan Ibrahimovic, Cristian Chivu and Luis Figo because of injury while Nicolas Burdisso, Dejan Stankovic and Olivier Dacourt are doubts. Second-placed AS Roma, three points behind Inter, should welcome back Philippe Mexes for the visit of Atalanta after the French centre back was suspended for Thursday's Italian Cup semi-final victory over Catania. Striker Francesco Totti, ruled out until next season after a knee operation, has been fined 10,000 euros ($15,330) after saying Inter had received "little bits of help" from referees, the Italian soccer federation said in a statement. Fourth-placed AC Milan, a point ahead of Fiorentina in the race for the final Champions League qualifying slot, have midfielder Andrea Pirlo banned for the trip to Napoli. Silvio Berlusconi has formally resigned as Milan president, as he had to under law, following his swearing in as Italian prime minister for a third time. Fiorentina are without suspended duo Adrian Mutu and Manuel Pasqual for the home game with third bottom Parma. Hector Cuper's Parma will be relegated after 18 years in the top flight if they lose and other results go against them. "I didn't come to Parma to hibernate," striker Cristiano Lucarelli, who joined in January from Shakhtar Donetsk, told the club Web site (www.fcparma.com) Bottom club Livorno must win at home to Torino in order to keep alive their faint hopes of survival after four seasons in Serie A. The task has been made more difficult by six players being banned after last Sunday's 3-2 defeat at Atalanta when several Livorno players tried to storm the opposition dressing room. Atalanta's Simone Padoin had grabbed the late winning goal
